Description: Jackson USA Polka Dot Randy Rhoads Production Model. If you want a polka dot USA made Randy Rhoads Jackson this is the one. I’ve done research and contacted Jackson and from what I can find out this is a production model and was made in the late nineties most likely 1998. This guitar shows some signs of honest play but not abused, I believe in full disclosure and tried to picture everything that I can see on the the guitar, please email me with any questions please. On the top edge of the neck there is a paint chip which I pictured, there is not a crack in the wood just a chip in the paint and I tried to capture the chip in the picture. The tip of the headstock has a chip, between the pickups there is a very small imperfection in the paint. I put a pick next to the flaw to show scale looks like a small ding but there is not indentation and is so small you wouldn’t see this unless you were meticulously inspecting. Like I said the guitar has been played but man it’s a nice guitar. Features dimarzio pickups just like Randy’s V and based on the sticker the bridge a Dimarzio super distortion and the neck did not have a sticker but based on my research it might be a Dimarzio Jazz pickup but I’m not sure, I took a picture of both pickups. Includes trem bar and non original hard shell case. Please email if you have any questions.
Title: Jackson Polka Dot Randy Rhoads Jackson Flying V made In USA
